I

1 Sweet songstress, that unseen, unknown,
2 Dost strain thy little heaving breast,
3 Why dost thou wander still alone,
4 Wakeful, while other songsters rest?

II

5 Oft have I linger'd in the grove,
6 Charm'd with thy soothing, melting song;
7 It told---or seem'd to tell---of love---
8 Nor was the night, tho' darksome, long.

